Gulf Stocks: Aldar Properties and First Gulf Bank

-- B y   Z a h r a   H a n k i r
-- 
2011-02-21T10:47:58Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/gulf-stocks-aldar-properties-and-first-gulf-bank.html
Dubai’s  DFM General Index  lost 1.3
percent to 1,516.43, the lowest since Sept. 2, at the 2 p.m.
close in the emirate. Abu Dhabi’s  ADX General Index  dropped 0.5
percent and Oman’s MSM30 Index lost 0.9 percent.  The following stocks rose or fell in the Gulf. Symbols are
in parentheses.       Aldar Properties PJSC (ALDAR UH) declined to the lowest
this month, retreating 2.9 percent to 1.65 dirhams. Abu Dhabi’s
biggest developer postponed its extraordinary general meeting to
Feb. 27 due to a lack of quorum.       First Gulf Bank PJSC (FGB UH) decreased to the lowest in
almost three weeks, dropping 1.2 percent to 17.15 dirhams. The
lender controlled by Abu Dhabi’s ruling family plans to list 125
million new shares on the  Abu Dhabi  stock exchange today after
converting 3.6 billion dirhams ($980 million) of convertible
bonds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zahra Hankir in Dubai at 
 zhankir@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  